- "Case fatality rate" is the ratio of the number of deaths to the total number of cases, expressed as a percentage;
- "Test positivity rate" is the ratio of positive tests to the total number of tests, expressed as a percentage;
- "Vaccination rate" is the ratio of the total number of doses administered to the population of the region, expressed as a percentage;
- "Active case rate" is the ratio of active cases to the population of the region, expressed as a percentage.

- "new active cases" refers to cases that are both new and active;
- "case rate" is calculated as the total number of new active cases divided by the sum of the region's population and the total number of vaccinations, expressed as a percentage;
- The query provides insights into the impact of population and vaccination rates on the incidence of new active cases over time.

sql:
SELECT MAX(total_cases) AS highest_case_count
FROM (
    SELECT region_id, SUM(case_count) AS total_cases
    FROM cases
    GROUP BY region_id
) AS region_totals;

